      • move

        public void move(RuleConditionLine line,
                 RuleConditionLine otherLine)

        Moves line's position within a list. line is moved to the position of otherLine, with all lines in between shifting either up or down, depending on whether line is being moved down or up the list, respectively. In other words, after a "move", the list looks as if the line had been temporarily removed and then re-inserted after otherLine.

      • refresh

        public KeyableBean refresh()
        Refreshes this bean with the latest database version.

        This method does nothing if the bean is edited or inserted in its current bundle. If the bean no longer exists in the database, then null is returned. If the bean has been evicted from its bundle, then null is returned. Otherwise, this bean is returned, with its contents updated.

        Specified by:

        public void remove()
        Marks this bean for remove. A bean marked for remove will be deleted or retired when the transaction is committed. Once a bean is marked for remove, it cannot be switched to update, edit, or read.

      • renameSymbol

        public void renameSymbol(RuleContextDefinitionProvider contextDefinitionProvider,
                         java.lang.String oldSymbol,
                         java.lang.String newSymbol,
                         boolean renameTriggeredBySelf)
        Replace any occurrences of oldSymbol with newSymbol. Note that this does not simply do a textual search and replace, but attempts to only rename actual references to a context symbol - partial matches will not be replaced. 
         Examples:
  (claim, claim2): claim.Prop -> claim2.Prop
  (claim, claim2): claim1.Prop -> claim1.Prop
  (claim, claim2): claimMethod() -> claimMethod()

      • touch

        public void touch()
        Set's the version of the bean to the next value (i.e. the bean version original value+1) Multiple calls to this method on the same bean will result in the same value being used for the version (i.e. it is idempotent). Calling this method will force the bean to be written to the database and participate fully in the commit cycle e.g. pre-update rules will be run, etc.
        Specified by:
        touch in interface Versionable
